     1	## Accepted Claims
     2	
     3	### C1 — Remove duplicate proactive permission comment
     4	**File**: packages/core/src/sandbox/utils/proactivePermissions.ts:74
     5	**Change**: Delete one of the two identical JSDoc blocks immediately preceding `getProactiveToolSuggestions`.
     6	**Goal link**: This clarifies the proactive permission helper introduced for sandbox usability.
     7	**Justification**: Removing the duplicated comment preserves behavior while eliminating accidental copy-paste noise around the core new helper.
     8	
     9	### C2 — Drop redundant workspace equality check
    10	**File**: packages/core/src/policy/policy-engine.ts:667
    11	**Change**: In the additional-permission workspace guard, replace the condition `!isSubpath(workspace, p) && workspace !== p` with `!isSubpath(workspace, p)`.
    12	**Goal link**: This clarifies the goal of requiring explicit confirmation for additional permission paths outside the workspace.
    13	**Justification**: `isSubpath(workspace, p)` already returns true when the two paths are equal, so the extra equality check adds no behavior and makes the boundary rule harder to read.
    14	
    15	### C3 — Gate proactive suggestions after command need is known
    16	**File**: packages/core/src/tools/shell.ts:257
    17	**Change**: In `ShellToolInvocation.shouldConfirmExecute`, parse the command and call `isNetworkReliantCommand(rootCommand, subCommand)` before awaiting `getProactiveToolSuggestions(rootCommand)`, and only fetch suggestions inside the `needsNetwork` branch.
    18	**Goal link**: This keeps proactive permission checks focused on commands that actually need expanded sandbox access.
    19	**Justification**: The current order probes home/cache paths for commands such as `npm test` that will not use the result, so moving the suggestion lookup behind the existing need check removes unnecessary work without changing confirmation outcomes.
